Title: Foster Gravity Traverses, Warragul, EL4810, EL3706, 2004 Vic (P200432), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This Foster Gravity Traverses, Warragul, EL4810, EL3706, 2004 Vic (P200432) contains a total of 1068 point data values acquired at a spacing between 25 and 500 metres. The data is located in VIC and were acquired in 2004, under project No. 200432 for Sedimentary Holdings Ltd.

Lineage: This Foster Gravity Traverses, Warragul, EL4810, EL3706, 2004 Vic (P200432), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the Foster Gravity Traverses, Warragul, EL4810, EL3706, 2004 Vic (P200432) survey acquired for Sedimentary Holdings Ltd. This dataset contains a total of 1068 point data values. The data is located in VIC and were acquired in 2004. The point located data were collected in irregular traverses layout at a station spacing between 25 and 500 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Reference: Intrepid Geophysics, http://www.intrepid-geophysics.com.

Lineage: This EL2639 Oakden Hills, SA Gravity Survey 2002A7 (P200250), gravity point data contains ground gravity point data for the EL2639 Oakden Hills, SA Gravity Survey 2002A7 (P200250) survey acquired for Gunson Resources Ltd. This dataset contains a total of 579 point data values. The data is located in SA and were acquired in 2002. The point located data were collected in grid layout at an average station spacing of 2000 metres. Terrain corrections were calculated using the INTREPID Geophysics software package. The processed data are checked by GA geophysicists using standard methods for assessing quality to ensure that the final data are fit-for-purpose. All data are provided in EPSG:4283 coordinates, Australian Height Datum (AHD) and gravity datum of AAGD07. The units are degrees, meters, and micrometres per second squared, respectively. Title: SA Gravity Survey 2006A2 (P200651), gravity point data
Abstract: Gravity data measures small changes in gravity due to changes in the density of rocks beneath the Earth's surface. The data collected are processed via standard methods to ensure the response recorded is that due only to the rocks in the ground. The results produce datasets that can be interpreted to reveal the geological structure of the sub-surface. The processed data is checked for quality by GA geophysicists to ensure that the final data released by GA are fit-for-purpose. This SA Gravity Survey 2006A2 (P200651) contains a total of 147 point data values acquired at a spacing of 1000 metres. The data is located in SA and were acquired in 2006, under project No. 200651 for None.
